
Q. Explain ClassCastException with the help of the example.

Ans => We can downcast the parent class variable to the child class object 
       only if the parent class variable point to the child class object, 
       otherwise it will throw a runtime exception called ClassCastException.
       
Example:-

public class Animal{
          void state(){
              System.out.prinln("Animal is running");          
           }
       }
       class Tiger extends Animal{
          void state{
            System.out.prinln("Tiger is running");
          }
          void eat{
            System.out.prinln("Tiger is eating");
          }
       }
       
       //From the main method 
       Animal a1 = new Animal();
       a1.eat(); //ClasscastException
       
       
       